# Python Constants Naming

Use **UPPER_SNAKE_CASE** for module-level constants (including public and
private): e.g. `PYPROJECT_TOML`, `FILE_INFO`, `_DEFAULT_EXCLUDES`.

This matches the style used in `_config.py`, `_files.py`, `messages.py`, and
`_stub.py`.
